@node "MARKIEREN" "Selecting Files"

 @{b}Selecting Files@{ub}
 ===============

 Select one single file by clicking it once.

 There are two ways of selecting multiple files:

 · Keep left mouse button pressed and drag a frame around
   the files. When releasing the mouse button, all files
   inside the frame get selected.

 · Keep shift key pressed and click files once.

 Hint:
 If you want to drag multiple selected files onto the AppIcon,
 remember to keep the shift key pressed while dragging.

@endnode

@node "NEUES" "New in this Version"
@prev "WARNUNG"
@next "VORWORT"

 @{b}What's New in this Version?@{ub}
 ===========================

 · If you drag only one icon onto the packing AppIcon,
   Peperoni uses the original name for the new archive.

 · Executables for 68040 CPUs included.
   Reason: One user reported Peperoni to crash on his
   060-equipped system (guru #8000000B - «illegal
   opcode»), whereas a program version compiled for
   68040 CPUs was reported to run flawlessly.

@endnode

@node "GESCHICHTE" "What has happened until now?"
@prev "ZUKUNFT"
@next "KONTAKT"

 @{b}8 The History of Peperoni@{ub}
 =========================

 _________________________
 Version 1.5e (05/10/98): \\______________________________

    · If you drag only one icon onto the packing AppIcon,
      Peperoni uses the original name for the new archive.

    · Executables for 68040 CPUs included.
      Reason: One user reported Peperoni to crash on his
      060-equipped system (guru #8000000B - «illegal
      opcode»), whereas a program version compiled for
      68040 CPUs was reported to run flawlessly.


 _________________________
 Version 1.5d (04/13/98): \\______________________________

    · Finally won the battle against a totally idiotic
      but remarkably resistant bug which would block
      some applications

    · Changed the internal creation of new archive's
      file names as ZIP refuses to add its suffix
      to file names containing a dot ».«


 _________________________
 Version 1.5c (03/03/98): \\______________________________

 ************** inofficial testing version **************

    · Added the translator's name to the »About...«
      window


 _________________________
 Version 1.5b (02/21/98): \\______________________________

 ************** inofficial testing version **************

    · Localization; contact me via email if you like to
      translate

    · AppIcons' labels can be changed, therefore added
      two new @{"Tooltypes" link "TOOLTYPES" 0}

    · Redesigned the preferences window

    · Peperoni now recognizes its actual file name. So
      go ahead and rename it, if you think you have to.

    · Not storing path information when packing should
      work for LZX

    · Stopped overwriting unknown Tooltypes. DONOTWAIT
      will never be deleted again!

    · Should produce no more Enforcer hits

    · Implemented error handling


 _________________________
 Version 1.4a (01/29/98): \\______________________________

 ************** inofficial testing version **************

    · Rewrote the program from scratch; couldn't maintain
      the original one-file source any more.
      Regularly crashes on quitting. This was the
      beginning of some lovely weeks I spent debugging.

    · Severe problems concerning power supply; removed
      the coffee feature again

 _________________________
 Version 1.3a (12/05/97): \\______________________________

 ************** inofficial testing version **************

    · First approach to localization

    · Added function for making coffee


 ________________________
 Version 1.2 (11/30/97): \\_______________________________

    · Cancelling the file requesters now also cancels the
      whole procedure; Peperoni ignored this before.

    · Changing the AppIcon's positions is accepted while
      running, no need for restarting the program.

    · Added shortcuts for the «Quit», «Save», «Use», and
      «Cancel» buttons.


 ________________________
 Version 1.1 (11/26/97): \\_______________________________

 ************** inofficial testing version ************** 

    · Added positioning of the AppIcons, therefore
      had to extend the GUI and add four new
      @{"Tooltype" link "TOOLTYPES" 0} entries.

    · Now files will be packed together with their icons.
      Pardon me, just forgot about them.

    · Progress window now also displays names of
      directories when packing.

    · When packing to an asked destination, you may
      specify a name for the new archive. But you
      don't have to.

    · Fixed LZX calling. LZX appends automatically appends
      a slash to directories. Result was: «...//...».
      That's why it also packed the whole parent directory.

    · Close gadget and Esc key now only close the settings
      window, whereas Peperoni keeps on running.

    · Added «Quit» button.


 ________________________
 Version 1.0 (11/06/97): \\_______________________________

 ************ First version and first release ***********

@endnode
